Description: Eastman 905CE in beautiful tobacco sunburst. All solid woods, carved maple back and carved spruce top. Figured maple binding throughout, even in the F holes. I purchased this guitar new in 2010 after considering American made and other Asian brands. A comparable American made guitar would cost well over $5000, but this instrument is everything you could ask for; easy playing, well balanced up and down the neck, beautiful tone, excellent volume and projection from a 16” body. I upgraded the pickup from the stock Asian produced “Kent Armstrong designed” pickup to an authentic Kent Armstrong which I ordered direct. The stock pickup is included. The guitar is in overall good condition with minor fret wear and a few dings/chips I was able to capture in the photos and some light scratches on the bottom from a guitar stand. I’ve owned many high-end guitars and none of them matched this Eastman in quality workmanship and choice materials. It is a beautiful looking and sounding instrument. This guitar is of course suitable for a variety of jazz music, but also sounds great for acoustic blues and Americana. I will include a new set of the strings of your choice with the neck appropriately adjusted and the bridge position marked with tape.
Title: Eastman 905 CE Archtop Jazz Guitar
